LOWER BOUND

You are given a sorted array nums of length n and an integer x. Your task is to find the lower bound of x in the array.

The lower bound of x is defined as the smallest index i such that nums[i] is greater than or equal to x.

If no such index exists, return n (the size of the array).

The array is sorted in non-decreasing order.

FUNCTION DESCRIPTION

Function name: solve

This function finds the lower bound index of a given value in a sorted array.

PARAMETERS

nums
A sorted array of integers

x
The target integer

RETURN VALUE

Return the smallest index i such that nums[i] is greater than or equal to x
Return n if no such index exists

CONSTRAINTS

1 ≤ n ≤ 100000
-100000 ≤ nums[i], x ≤ 100000
nums is sorted in non-decreasing order

INPUT FORMAT

One line containing two integers n and x
One line containing n space-separated integers representing the sorted array

OUTPUT FORMAT

Print a single integer — the lower bound index

SAMPLE INPUT

6 7
2 4 6 8 10 12

SAMPLE OUTPUT

3

EXPLANATION

At index 3, the element 8 is the first number greater than or equal to 7

SAMPLE INPUT

5 -1
0 1 2 3 4

SAMPLE OUTPUT

0

EXPLANATION

All elements are greater than -1, so the lower bound is index 0

static int solve(int[] nums, int x) {
       int left=0;
       int right=nums.length-1;
       int a=nums.length;
       while(left<=right)
       {
           int mid=(left+right)/2;
           if(nums[mid]>=x)
           {
             a=mid;
             right=mid-1;
           }else{
               left=mid+1;
           }
       } 
        return a;
    }
    
    
    
